@startuml
skinparam componentStyle uml2

title WebFOCUS to PostgreSQL Transpiler System Overview

package "Frontend" {
    [ANTLR4 Parser] as Parser
    [WebFOCUS Grammar] as Grammar
    note right of Parser
        **Open Points:**
        * Migrate core parser from Lark to ANTLR4 (3.1)
        * Implement ANTLR4 Lexer/Parser in Python (3.1.2)
        * Integrate ANTLR4 into WebFocusParser dispatcher (3.1.3)
        * Define Dialogue Manager grammar (-SET, -IF, etc.) (3.2, 1.3)
        * Support -SET command and ampersand variables (1.3.1) - [DONE]
        * Support Labels and -GOTO (1.3.2.1) - [DONE]
        * Support HEADING and other formatting commands (3.4.9) - [DONE]
        * Support COMPUTE command for calculated fields (3.4.10) - [DONE]
        * Support Expressions and WHERE clauses (3.5) - [DONE]
        * Complete Master File Grammar transition (1.1) - [DONE]
        * Port WebFOCUS Report Grammar to ANTLR4 (1.2) - [DONE]
        * Ensure Unified Lexer/Parser handles interleaved code (1.4)
        * Reverse engineer and document syntax/behavior (1.4)
    end note
}

package "Semantic Analysis" {
    [ASG Builder] as ASGBuilder
    [Symbol Table] as SymbolTable
    note right of ASGBuilder
        **Open Points:**
        * Implement Abstract Semantic Graph (ASG) (4.1)
        * Define ASG node classes (4.1.1, 2.1)
        * Define Data Model ASG nodes (2.1.2) - [DONE]
        * Define Procedural ASG nodes (2.1.3) - [DONE]
        * Implement Symbol Table for scope/type tracking (4.1.2, 2.2) - [DONE]
        * Implement ASG builder from ANTLR4 AST (4.1.3) - [DONE]
        * Implement Type Inference (2.3)
    end note
}

package "Optimization" {
    [SSA IR Generator] as IRGen
    [Optimizer] as Optimizer
    note right of IRGen
        **Open Points:**
        * Develop SSA-based Intermediate Representation (IR) (4.2)
        * Define IR instruction set and CFG structure (4.2.1)
        * Implement CFG generator from ASG (4.2.2, 3.1)
        * Implement SSA transformation (phi-nodes, renaming) (4.2.3, 3.2)
        * Implement basic optimization passes (DCE, CP) (4.2.4)
        * Implement set-based optimization for TABLE FILE (4.3, 3.3)
    end note
}

package "Backend" {
    [Jinja2 Emitter] as Emitter
    [PL/pgSQL Templates] as Templates
    note right of Emitter
        **Open Points:**
        * Implement PL/pgSQL Emitter using Jinja2 (5.1)
        * Setup Jinja2 environment and base templates (5.1.1, 4.1)
        * Implement emitter for TABLE FILE relational logic (5.1.2, 4.2)
        * Implement emitter for Dialogue Manager procedural logic (5.1.3)
        * Map formatting commands to decoupled presentation logic (5.2, 4.3)
    end note
}

package "Tooling & Verification" {
    [CLI Tool] as CLI
    [Test Suite] as Tests
    [Doc Generator] as DocGen
    note right of Tests
        **Open Points:**
        * Create 'readthedocs' documentation (1.5)
        * Migrate Lark test cases to ANTLR4 (3.1.4, 5.1)
        * Integrate parser results into doc generator (6.1)
        * Develop CLI tool for code analysis (6.2)
        * Implement automated test runner for samples (6.3.2)
        * Verify grammar coverage against samples (6.3.3, 5.2)
        * Performance Benchmarking (5.3)
        * Remove Lark dependency (TECH_DEBT, 6.1)
        * Update tests to target ANTLR4 frontend (TECH_DEBT)
    end note
}

Grammar --> Parser
Parser --> ASGBuilder : AST
ASGBuilder --> IRGen : ASG
IRGen --> Optimizer : IR (CFG/SSA)
Optimizer --> Emitter : Optimized IR
Emitter --> Templates

@enduml
